08_get_freq


  1. Question

    A sinusoidal pure tone is generated by randomly choosing a frequency (\(F\)) in the following equation: \[y(t) ~=~ \cos(2\pi F t)\]


    As shown above, the curve has maximums at both \(t=0\) and \(t=0.94\). What is the frequency in Hz? The tolerance is \(\pm 0.01\) Hz.


    Solution

    Count how many periods occur between \(t=0\) and \(t=0.94\).


    Find the period.

    \[P = \frac{0.94 ~\mathrm{seconds}}{3~\mathrm{cycles}}\]

    The frequency is the reciprocal of the period.

    \[F ~=~ \frac{1}{P} ~=~ \frac{3~\mathrm{cycles}}{0.94 ~\mathrm{seconds}}\]

    \[F ~\approx~ 3.19 ~\mathrm{Hz}\]
